<div dir="ltr">I am seeing the following errors when using NAG Fortran (v5 or v6):<div><font face="monospace, monospace"><br></font></div><div><font face="monospace, monospace">Error: /sandbox/hargrove/OMPI/openmpi-2.0.0rc3-linux-x86_64-nagfor-5/openmpi-2.0.0rc3/ompi/mpi/fortran/use-mpi-tkr/mpi_comm_spawn_multiple_f90.f90: Argument 3 to MPI_COMM_SPAWN_MULTIPLE has data type DOUBLE PRECISION in reference from MPI_COMM_SPAWN_MULTIPLEN and CHARACTER in reference from MPI_COMM_SPAWN_MULTIPLEA<br>Error: /sandbox/hargrove/OMPI/openmpi-2.0.0rc3-linux-x86_64-nagfor-5/openmpi-2.0.0rc3/ompi/mpi/fortran/use-mpi-tkr/mpi_testall_f90.f90: Argument 4 to MPI_TESTALL has data type DOUBLE PRECISION in reference from MPI_TESTALLI and INTEGER in reference from MPI_TESTALLS</font><div><br></div><div>I am 99% certain this means the FC=-mismatch fix is missing.</div><div>To be precise, v2.x is missing <a href="https://github.com/open-mpi/ompi/commit/1ce5393f">https://github.com/open-mpi/ompi/commit/1ce5393f</a></div><div><br></div><div>-Paul<br clear="all"><div><br></div>-- <br><div class="gmail_signature" data-smartmail="gmail_signature"><div dir="ltr"><div><font face="courier new, monospace"><div>Paul H. Hargrove                          <a href="mailto:PHHargrove@lbl.gov" target="_blank">PHHargrove@lbl.gov</a></div><div>Computer Languages &amp; Systems Software (CLaSS) Group</div><div>Computer Science Department               Tel: +1-510-495-2352</div><div>Lawrence Berkeley National Laboratory     Fax: +1-510-486-6900</div></font></div></div></div>
